Q: What is Abstraction in OOP?
A: Abstraction exposes essential behavior while hiding unnecessary details. It's achieved via abstract classes, interfaces, and well-designed APIs.

Python:
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod
class Notifier(ABC):
 @abstractmethod
 def send(self, msg): ...

Java:
interface Notifier { void send(String msg); }

C++:
struct Notifier { virtual void send(const std::string&)=0; virtual ~Notifier()=default; };

