Difficulty: Beginner

Q: What is Composition over Inheritance in OOP?
A: Favor composition to assemble behaviors at runtime instead of deep inheritance hierarchies. Composition reduces coupling and avoids fragile base class problems.

Python:
class Car:
 def __init__(self, engine): self.engine=engine
 def drive(self): self.engine.run()

Java:
class Car { private Engine engine; Car(Engine e){this.engine=e;} void drive(){engine.run();} }

C++:
struct Car{ Engine engine; void drive(){ engine.run(); } };

