Q: What is Static vs Instance members in OOP?
A: Static members belong to the class, not instances; instance members are per-object. Static methods cannot access instance state unless an instance is provided.

Python:
class A: @staticmethod
 def util(): ...
 @classmethod
 def from_x(cls,x): return cls()

Java:
static int count; static void util(){}

C++:
struct A{ static int count; }; int A::count=0;

